  "texts": [
    "The result is an N x B array of data, where N is the number of unique suppliers.",
    "The two sets of transactions are multiplied by B to help preserve the relative covariances, though this is an optional operation.",
    "The percentage changes between each of the first B -1 columns with its adjacent column on the right are calculated.",
    "The resulting array C is now an N x (B-1) array.",
    "To ensure that the covariance matrix does not have too large a magnitude, the percentage changes are clipped to be between -100 and 100."
  ],
